reviews.review: Wanted to see more 'creatures' from other worlds. But it was still awesome. Not sure how Princess Leia's still in it but great to see old Han Solo again! And Luke and others, Ewoks,  Chewy, I'll love them forever!

It's a very fast paste movie, that really tries to give to the audience answers just for the sake of giving answers without any depth only to please the eye! However the real reason why I gave this movie a 2/5 is because of its inconcistency with the previous movies

LOL!!!! Fans wanted different after TFA and got TLJ. Hated TLJ because it's too different or more accurately, too smart for them. Disney decides to cave to fan service and feed them what they want, predictability. Fan reviews shows they love it while critics wanted more of what they loved about TLJ rather than JJ and company playing it safe! And thus they are split! This is funny! But whatever, I LOVED this trilogy and I love this film! TLJ is still a superior film but man, people, this isn't art house, this is space fantasy! Stop thinking too hard over Star Wars... because you haters are so in the minority!

I loved this "ending" to the skywalker saga. I've seen it twice and I will see it again in the theater, I'm sure. The official critics are panning this film, but the audience scores and reactions I've heard from people are all good.

We love Star Wars. I loved the storyline, characters and actors. For the new generation of kids and open minded adults there is plenty of opportunity for more stories to be developed. Many of us are stuck to our old beloved characters, but the new gen isn't, they roll with it.
A solid ending to the Skywalker saga!
They FINALLY recaptured the feeling of the first 2 movies. The nostalgia for all of us who were there for the originals will love this one!

Too much action and not enough plot followed by weird plot pacing. Add in major plot points that weren't developed at all in previous movies and seemed to come out of nowhere and you get a solid "just okay" movie.
It has a few plot twists that don't really make sense but what movie doesn't? Overall I think it was an amazing movie that met most of my expectations. I loved it!
